ve been reproduced. Eichler's empirical and theoretical study of masculinities in international relations applies for the first time the concept of "militarized masculinity," developed by feminist IR scholars, to the case of Russia.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aDraftxRussia (Federation). 0aDraftzRussia (Federation). 0aGender identityxRussia (Federation). 0aGender identityzRussia (Federation). 0aMasculinityxRussia (Federation). 0aMasculinityzRussia (Federation). 0aMilitarismxRussia (Federation). 0aMilitarismzRussia (Federation). 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477836740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804778367423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804778367.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles